 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
The host, Kapil Sharma makes a rocking entry to the stage and welcomes everyone to the show. He then proceeds to welcome the special guests for the night. They are none other than the star cast of the upcoming comedy film, Cirkus, starring Ranveer Singh, Jacqueline Fernandez, Pooja Hegde, and Varun Sharma. They are here to promote their film along with their director, Rohit Shetty who tells that the lead character was inspired by Ranveer's real-life personality and energy. To witness more, watch the episode now.

It is aired in Nepal Television at 8:50 PM and in YouTube at 9:30 PM every Tuesday. This show is produced by Media Hub Pvt. Ltd.

snippet.title: üí™C'mon! Learn How To Give CPR and Save Life - By Kishor Singh #shorts
snippet.description:
#shorts

For "HUGE" Discount on 3D Animation Course, Call: +91-99830-83303 or Click here üëâüèª https://professorofhow.com

C'mon! Learn How To Give CPR and Save Life - By Kishor Singh #shorts 

Heart attack is getting more common with time. Double-tap the screen and let's learn how to provide CPR if someone collapsed around you.
A sudden collapse happens during a heart attack. Your heart, which was supplying the oxygenated blood to your organs, will become unable to pump the blood anymore and the organs will start to die because of the deficiency of blood. Your heart is made to pump artificially in this situation so that your organs keep receiving blood until some medical help arrives.
In order to provide CPR, both the hands of the CPR provider should be placed at the lower middle part of the chest. The press should be hard enough to push the chest by 2 inches, and this pushing process should be fast enough to provide more than 100 compressions per minute. These compressions make the heart pump and the organs start to receive the blood.
If these compressions came out to be not so hard or fast enough, the body organs and especially the brain will not receive the blood and start to die within a few seconds.
After 30 compressions, mouth-to-mouth breathing should be given twice, and both of these steps should be repeated until the person gets some medical help or gets normal.
If you are also interested in making these kinds of informative 3D videos, hit the link given in the pinned comment.
